  "method": "We propose Parallel Speculative Drafting with Exact Verification. Maintain two models: a small draft model S and the target large model L. At each decoding iteration, S proposes a length-K continuation for the current context c, and L verifies that continuation in a single pass while guaranteeing the final token stream is an exact sample from L. The loop pipelines these stages so that while L verifies block b, S drafts block b+1 under the most recently accepted prefix.\n\nTo make S propose multiple future tokens in one forward pass, equip it with a lightweight two-stream, position-masked lookahead head. Given context c, S runs one shared backbone and emits logits for offsets 1..K simultaneously, with a position-specific mask that lets the t-th offset attend to c and previously proposed offsets <t but never to ≥t. This yields K draft tokens y1..yK in parallel. For longer horizons or multi-device setups, split the K positions into M shards and apply a Picard-style sweep: initialize a cache with S’s first pass proposals for all K positions; then in one or two additional parallel sweeps, each shard re-evaluates only its assigned positions while reading the others from the cache, improving self-consistency of the proposed block without serializing through time.\n\nVerification uses a single teacher-forced pass of L over c concatenated with the proposed block y1..yK. This pass returns the conditional distributions p_L(. | c, y< t) for all t=1..K at once. Traverse the block left-to-right and perform an acceptance–correction test that preserves L’s exact distribution: for each t, accept y_t with probability min(1, p_L(y_t | c, y< t) / p_S(y_t | c, y< t)), where p_S is S’s probability for the same conditional; if a token is rejected at position j, sample a correction token z_j from p_L(. | c, y< j) using the already-computed distribution, emit z_j, discard the remainder of the draft block, and resume the loop from the new context. If all K tokens pass, append the whole block. Because all acceptance and any needed correction draws at j come from L’s conditionals, the emitted stream is an exact sample from L with no quality loss.\n\nFor throughput, pipeline S and L and reuse KV caches. Choose K adaptively based on a short moving average of accepted tokens per verification, targeting high acceptance without over-proposing. Train S by distilling next-token and multi-step lookahead distributions from L, which raises acceptance rates. To cut L’s verification cost further, add a tiny per-layer predictor that gates FFN activations so L loads or computes only the small subset of active neurons during verification passes; this reduces memory traffic and FLOPs without changing L’s outputs.",
